Cassiel is the pseudonym for London, UK-based composer, performer, software architect and media artist Nick Rothwell. Cassiel projects generally involve collaboration with internationally-renowned choreographers and contemporary dance companies, such as Laurie Booth, Ballett Frankfurt, Russell Maliphant, Lea Anderson, Aydın Teker (İstanbul) and Random Dance Company (Sadler’s Wells).
  
  Cassiel plays live sets of pulse-based electronica utilising a variety of control surfaces and custom-designed software performance systems, with a musical style which shifts from Berlin-school to soothing ambient, tribal or glitch, but always with imaginative timbral design and strong harmonic structures. Cassiel has also composed commercially for television, radio and outdoor installations.
  
  Cassiel has worked at STEIM (Amsterdam), CAMAC (Paris), ZKM (Karlsruhe), Techne (İstanbul), Zodiak (Helsinki) and CIANT (Prague). He is a regular performer at the Different Skies festival (Arcosanti, Arizona) and is currently working with dance production company Body>Data>Space in London, Prague, Dresden and Paris.

Cicero Chaves, DJ and producer, began listening to electronic music in 1997. By the year 2000, he had already begun to produce his own tracks, making many different projects with different styles of music, from tech-house to hip-hop. He has also been a sound producer and a sound designer of soundtracks for films.
Nowadays, he spends his time between techno and its varieties and tech-house production. He has been, for some time now, perfecting his skills in production with DJ and Producer Krishna Baby.
Krishna began to listen to house and techno music at the age of fourteen, by the time he used to go to the clubs which started the underground electronic music scene in Rio de Janeiro.
In 2003, he started playing minimal and progressive, switching later to progressive house and tech-house, and has
been,for 4 years now, making his own music.About a year ago Cicero Chaves and Krishna Baby have started working together producing tracks, beggining their own project
called Freakslum.
Inspired by different styles and varieties of music, Freakslum has been creating its own musical identity, aiming always at a minimalistic and straight conception, very much influenced by American Techno and European Minimal, bringing thus to Rio de Janeiro a totally new concept in Techno and Tech House.

The name of Belgian artist and DJ Dopefish (who also goes by the name DJ System-D in drum and bass music), has been a force on the electronic, dance, hip-hop and drum and bass scenes in his native Belgium from 1992 on.

He is known for his wide-ranging sets that include everything from breaks, house/electro , baile funk and hip-hop, Miami bass and grime/dubstep, and capable of rockin’ all types of parties, from small hottest clubs to big festivals audiences! In addition to his formidable mixing and scratching skills, Dopefish is founder of his own label Dopefish A.U.D.I.O. he started in 2007. The label already includes no less than 25th releases so far. His production skills are eclectic but always effective and giving an energic party vibe.

Early 2009 he signed to the legendary UK based Y4K label for his debut album (release date : end 2009). Dopefish released two EP's on Y4K, "Big Bad Wolf" and "Housecalls EP". In addition of his work on Dopefish AUDIO and Y4K, he produced tracks for other labels such as RuNT Records, Bombeatz Music, Destination?, G Point Music,...

With a style based in percussive elements, and minimal influenced tech-house grooves, their live performances have recently been in demand by the most exclusive night clubs in Mexico City. This up & coming producer duo has quickly started to make some noise as one of the finest underground acts of the mexican scene. 

With remixes for labels such as Akbal Music (MX) and Proton Ltd (US) released in the past few months, Twilk have shown to be also talented at the studio. Their most recent work will be released soon in their debut EP on Akbal Music. 

The duo will spend the next months at the studio working on more original productions and remixes, as well as their constantly evolving live-act.

Resistance has been DJing for around 4 years, after discovering club night Tangled and buying a pair of old second hand Technics 1210 decks he began his quest to play bass bombs to the masses. After Tangled finished he started club night Carry On with Steve Thorpe (Tangled Breaks) and played every month along side artists such as Krafty Kuts, Elite Force, Rennie Pilgrem, Rico tubbs and The Soul of Man to name a few.

Now serving as Co-Owner, resident DJ and promotor at his Breakspoll Award Winning (best small club/event) clubnight Lowdown & Dirty with Steve Thorpe, Ash Howell and Mark Mciver, playing alongside people such as Hybrid (Live) Scratch Perverts, Freestylers, Plump DJs, Stanton Warriors, Meat Katie & more, expect to hear a full flavour and his own edits and remixes of bass heavy electronic music whether it be Techno-Electro-Breabeat-House or anything else that takes his fancy. Having played in the U&A Recordings bigtop at Wickerman festival and being involved with the label and also spinning at the U&A Boat Party afterparty with Peo De Pitte, Mike Hulme, Zodiac Cartel & the Loops of Fury, and on the Blow dance stage at the Kendal Calling festival, Parklife Festival, Eurocultured Festival,  as well as currently studying a full time music producer course, Resistance continues to develop his sound and put on huge parties in the UK.

Der in München lebende DJ und Produzent Finley Forsythe hat sich bereits im frühen Kindesalter sehr für Musik interessiert. Die Mutter spielte Gitarre, die Schwester Querflöte und der Bruder Klavier.

Im Alter von 12 Jahren bekam Finley seine erste Gitarre von der Mutter geschenkt und nahm einige Jahre professionellen Gitarrenunterricht. In den weiteren Verlauf folgten Auftritte mit der Rockband "Psycho Peanuts".

Im Jahr 2006 steckte sich Finley mit dem Housemusik-Virus an. Zeitgleich machte Finley erste Gehversuche als DJ auf Partys von Freunden und kleineren Festen.

Mit 18 Jahren verlegte Finley Forsythe seinen Wohnsitz von seinem Geburtsort - der Stadt Lindau am Bodensee nach München, um sich am SAE-Institute zum Audio-Engineer ausbilden zu lassen. Finley lernte die Großstadt München kennen.

Gepackt vom Münchener Nachtleben und der Liebe zur elektronischen Tanzmusik gründete Finley das DJ Kingdom München zusammen mit DJ Waxford. Selbstproduzierte Tracks sind derzeit in Arbeit und folgen im Sommer 2010.

Started playing guitar at 14 in different rock bands around Madrid.When I was 19 I became really interested in jazz style, that was the beginning of my musical studies.I got into a jazz school and started playing in some bands, getting in love forever with the music of Miles , Hancock and Coltrane.Then move to Holland to study jazz guitar in the Royal Conservatory of The Hague where everything started to change.My approach to the music and the way of making it started to change.I met wonderful people there who made me understand music and spirituality.At that point I was crazy with all soulful black music , soul, funk, blues, reggae, so decided to buy a bass.That changed the whole thing.I was crazy with grooves and got deep into rythm.From that point electronic music appeared in my life. After few years exploring the worlds of jazz, soul & funk, started messing around with computers and electronics, becoming more interested in styles like broken beat, house, drum n 'bass and different forms of electronic music. Huge respect to all the people out there bringing truth, soul & beauty to the music.Love you all.

Age equals courage. When you are old and experienced, you no longer think about what others consider good, new or cool. You just take what's best from the years of music and make it your own. Fearless! If it works, it works. 

The three men of Mvsevm could be techno retirees, but these men got together to stitch up beats, bleeps and blissful synth interludes that would light up the bleakest of the Dark Ages. The sound is massive and minimal at the same time, the beats flutter ahead rigid as a North Korean military parade yet the groove is elastic like that of virgin leggings. Contradictions! When you've lived long enough, you embrace them rather than fear them. 

You smell the dust as the bones of the thin-limbed composers creak, but the perspective of these geezers ensures a ride as exhilirating as... well, whatever the teens these days do for kicks. 

Better to be a reborn has-been than a dead-end wannabe.

                1988 Didier Vanelli participate at the first "UMM" house party has Rimini (Italy) and returns in 1992 for the second session and the "Fete Stryctly Rhythm" in the same city, this is a moment he meets all label artists with whom he has played during this event.

I like to be introduced as a "MUSICAL TRAVEL-AGENT".
ONSTAGE I'm mostly playing an Easel K (Buchla Modular Synth) and The Pipe (from SOMA Lab) which allows mouth-synthesis... I also manipulate unique vinyls with my sounds/musics, assaulting turntables to take advantage of the vinyl material to fondle released sounds, raking the needle across the record's grooves, rubbing their stylus on paper, cardboard, metal to process unusual noises and textures. I have a physical relation to my recordings and envision my live sets like performances. 
Gesture is also a very important part of my compositional process... While composing I am also relying on the use of real instruments such as Cymbalom, Pianos, Guitar and Percs that I play like a kid discovering a new toy, improvising and attaching great importance to gesture and stressing dynamics. My moves aren’t consensual, not cozying up potential listeners. A Punky approach even if throughout the past years I have been following courses of Composition + Electroacoustic Music at the Conservatory, specializing in Modular Synthesis. 
Pushing further my research in bringing together the Human and its Machine into a tapestry of sound which creates a deep sound assemblage of exotic Musiques Concrètes which guarantees to grow on you with repeated listens, slowly revealing its detailed richness…

If you combine an addiction to vinyl with a decade of experience in the music industry with the respect and recognition from her peers and a residency with ‘The Likes Of You’...then what do you have?  You’ll end up with Melbourne’s one and only; Virginia Le.
At only 25 years of age, Melbourne’s shining star of tech already has an unparalleled history of achievement behind her.  Having learned her craft on the turntables at the tender age of 17, since then Virginia has paired her love of any and all musical elements with passion, drive, determination and technical prowess to forge a path in the industry that’s the envy of many.
Renowned for her uncanny ability to discover and premiere unheard gems, Virginia is also recognised as possessing unmatched radar for discovering amazing new tunes and incorporating them into her trademark super-tight and deeply rocking sets; her track selection and programming are second to none and are at the core of what defines her as one of Australia’s fastest rising talents within the electronic music scene.
As an original and pioneering resident of Australia’s best and most widely recognisable touring club night ‘The Likes Of You’, Virginia has amassed an incredible resume of events and club residencies which has seen her support and play alongside the biggest names in tech and house, including - Joris Voorn, Sven Vath, Aril Brikha, Steve Bug, Ame, Dixon, Nathan Fake, Vince Watson, Gui Boratto, John Tejada, Sasha, Justin Martin, James Holden, Danny Howells, Josh Wink, James Holden, Seth Troxler, Agoria, Richie Hawtin, Loco Dice, Spirit Catcher, Stacey Pullen, Carl Craig, Oliver Huntermann, Mathew Jonson, Paul Kalkbrenner Phonique, Format B, Luciano, Trentemoller, SuperMayer, Vincenzo, Alex Smoke, Martin Buttrich, Jamie Jones, Hybrid, Bart Skills, Superflu, Mark Romboy, Stephan Bodzin, Oxia, Sasha, John Digweed, Tiefschwarz, Justin Martin, Lutzenkirchen, Spiritcatcher, Norman Jay and Ewan Pearson.
Virginia Le has come to epitomise the very definition of substance over style; of production over glitz; and of professionalism over pretension – and her astounding list of festival appearances and A-list support slots speaks volumes of her skill behind the ones and twos.  Once you’ve been lucky enough to experience the magic she brings to her sets you’ll clearly see why Virginia is considered a Queen of underground...

Yamez is a leading DJ, producer, and turntablist for Trap, EDM, Hip-Hop, Drum and Bass, and Open Format. He has won multiple DJ battles, DJ’d radio shows, performed at parties for MTV, BMW,  and has held residencies at Webster Hall with Vashtie, Marquee, The DL with Stretch Armstrong, and Pacha, among others. He has toured over fifteen countries with world renowned artists including Trey Songz, Miguel, Elle Varner, and Azealia Banks, and has performed at Radio City Music Hall with Nas.

After winning several DJ battles in Pittsburgh and Amherst in the early 2000’s, Yamez was noticed by the X-Ecutioners, a world renowned turntablist crew formed in 1989. The members of the X-Ecutioners, including Grandmaster Roc Raida, DJ Precision, DJ Total Eclipse, and Boogie Blind, became Yamez’s mentors. Through their guidance, Yamez began his journey of mastery as a skilled turntablist and DJ. 

In 2004, Yamez joined the X-Ecutioners in over 10 cities on the DUB Magazine tour, a famed car magazine tour featuring artists such as T.I, Yin Yang Twins, and The Clipse. 

Yamez became an official Red Bull DJ from 2006-2016 and was an A and R (Mr. X) for Red Bull Music Academy from 2010-2015. During this period he DJ’d exclusive events and scouted, curated, and organized events for Red Bull Music Academy and discovered talent. 

From 2012-2013, Yamez toured with Trey Songz on his Chapter V Tour featuring Miguel and Elle Varner, and with Azealia Banks in 2015. Aside DJ’ing Banks’ shows in over 15 countries, Yamez also remixed exclusive tracks for Banks on the fly, and notably produced a track for her and Rick Ross called “Big Talk.”

Between 2017 to 2019, Yamez has been featured in a Boiler Room event at the Highline Ballroom, a Heineken event featuring Roy Woods,  V/BMW launch party. He DJ’s international private events and parties, and is a regular at New York’s most beloved venues. 

Yamez  has toured with Donnis, Stalley, & Ninjasonik, and has toured with World of Drum & Bass and Summer Jam. He has DJ’d for Moto X, Maloof Money Cup, Manny Mania Pro Skate Contest, and has opened for DJ Craze, French Montana, Asap Rocky, Scarface,Yo Gotti, Baauer, Bobby Shmurda, Afropunk and Craig David, Usher, Fabolous, Mobb Deep, Wu-Tang Clan, Danny Brown, Chief Keef, Maroon 5, Flosstradamus, and rocked Radio City Hall on NYE 2012 with Nas.

He has been featured on countless parties including events for Alife, Adidas, Nike, Reebok, Asap Rocky’s Birthday and New Years party, and many more. 


He has had brand sponsorships with ALIFE, Ray Ban, HUF, 10 DEEP, Lafayette, and El Señor. 


To contact Yamez and for booking inquiries contact Djyamez1@gmail.com

“Cactus Lizard” is the initial track on “Bobby Barbados”, and it showcases a very interesting musical style. Von Davis creates a folky, singer-songwriter type of music but creates a narrative style that is not typically present in this style of music. “Cactus Lizard” discusses the quandary of being a lizard where everyone else is a cactus, allowing Von Davis to add a little bit of Mexican influence to the track. The track gradually increases in speed with the danger felt by Von Davis’ character, until that point when “Clouds of Poison” starts up. “Clouds of Poison” is a track that drastically increases the technical complexity of “Bobby Barbados”, blending together drums, guitar, and bass into a scintillating track that shifts back and forth between the constituent elements acting in a harmonious and a dissonant way.

While there is not as much of a narrative aspect to “Clouds of Poison”, the track is as important as “Cactus Lizard” because it shows that what Von Davis is doing here is testing the boundaries of what is possible with music. While few individuals would link what Von Davis is doing during “Bobby Barbados” to post-modern classical composers, I see some similarity in “Bobby Barbados” to what Kryzsztof Pendrecki, John Cage, or Philip Glass have done in the last forty years. Where Cage used silence and Pendrecki did works based on Hiroshima, Von Davis is destroying assumptions and creating something completely new in each track on “Bobby Barbados”. There are tracks that would work in traditional conceptions of pop music on “Bobby Barbados” – the building speed and gravity of “Pickle Jar” is but an example – but taken together, what listeners will find on “Bobby Barbados” is nothing short of a re-envisioning of what music is and what music can be used to do.

“Humans” has a shuffling style to it that frames Von Davis’ vocals in a different way, moving from the singer-songwriter tag to something that is much more closely oriented to beat poetry than traditional music. Camren Von Davis has a great career ahead of him, and subsequent albums will undoubtedly continue to expand upon the narrative style that was first created during “Bobby Barbados”. If you want your mind, as well as what you feel that music can do and what it can say, find a way to purchase Camren Von Davis’ “Bobby Barbados”. You will not regret it.

Originally from outside Boston, Incyde first became involved in electronic music through his work as label manager of Scuba's Hotflush Recordings label in London in 2007, where he began playing at clubs and radio shows around the city's thriving dubstep scene. In 2008 he moved to New York City and became a resident deejay of America's founding dubstep night, Dub War, where he developed a reputation for his tasteful selection and genre-bending explorations into bass music. Focusing more energy on enhancing his sets there, Incyde's original productions were first met with support by Mary Anne Hobbs of BBC Radio 1 and Scuba in 2010. His debut, "Axis" was released on Hotflush's BACK AND 4TH compilation in April 2011, followed by the four-track "Telophase" EP on Brendon Moeller's Steadfast Records in August. Later that year, his rework of "Lost Highway" by Badawi (Raz Mesinai) was featured in Scuba's DJ-Kicks compilation on !K7 Records. He spent the next ten years being a grown-up on the remote island of Maui, Hawaii, and now lives outside Dallas, Texas.

Irish born Kim Carroll is a 2009
 Sundance Composer fellow and was awarded 'Gold medal of excellence' for the music he wrote for the thriller 'The Colony' at the 2008 Park City Film Music festival in Utah. He co-wrote the music for the film 'The Uninvited' with Harry Gregson-Williams (Shrek, Man on Fire, Narnia), has written music for RTE's 'PrimeTime', HBO's Addiction, NBC's Crossing Jordan, CBS ColdCase, VH1's Celebrity Fit Club, and Fox Sports. In addition, Carroll wrote the music for the feature-length documentary films "Survival of the Wildebeest" and the Sundance feature "The Horse Boy" w/ Lili Haydn. His latest scores were for the crime drama 'Across the Line (The Exodus of Charlie Wright)' starring Aidan Quinn, Andy Garcia, and Gina Gershon, and the drama/comedy "Congratulations".
 
 Carroll's music credits include Sinead O' Connor, Train, Paul Buchanan/Blue Nile, and Gary Jules (#1 UK hit with the song 'Mad World' from the film Donnie Darko). He can also be heard on the soundtracks for The Town, Gone,Baby,Gone, The Chronicles of Narnia(Prince Caspian), Veronica Guerin, Domino, and The Rundown. He is currently co-writing an album of original music with Lisbeth Scott (vocalist on Munich, Narnia, Passion of the Christ) to be released early next year.

I’m an experimental/improvising musician, playing guitar, bass, synth/keyboard, flute, hand percussion, computer, and recording devices… I sing, play, write, and produce, and I will try anything musical at least once… My musical and intellectual interests run to the outside of normal…

My head is way too big for my body, so I employ specially-trained birds to carry it aloft in a sling while I weave and slide along the less-travelled paths… I know where the secret treasure is buried, and I’m not telling anyone ever, unless they ply me with chocolate buddhas and dervish music…

Some favorites include, in no particular order: Gong, Daevid Allen, Steve Hillage, Brian Eno, Fennesz, Minamo, Tape, David Rothenberg, Fred Frith, Bill Frisell, Marc Ribot, Sun Ra, John Cage, Terry Riley, Harry Partch, Lou Harrison, Soft Boys, Yes, Peter Gabriel, King Crimson, Trance Mission, Cul De Sac, Grateful Dead, Laurie Anderson, Talking Heads, XTC, Sheila Chandra, Hermeto Pascoal, John Coltrane, Charles Mingus, Jethro Tull, Muddy Waters, Begona Olavide/Mudejar, Jordi Savall, Abdelkrim Rais, David Dunn, Radiohead, Guided By Voices, Bach, Tallis, Byrd, Steve Tibbetts, Tinariwen, Takagi Masakatsu, Juana Molina, and many, many more…

Fracture is a connoisseur of fine cuisine and hot sauces. When he’s not in the kitchen, he can be found running the Astrophonica label and releasing on pioneering British dance music labels such as Metalheadz and Exit Records.

As for the music Fracture makes, it isn’t easily categorisable. You can hear his blend of traditional aesthetics and new sounds in the 2012 underground smash ‘Get Busy’, for dBridge’s Exit Records, his 2013 low slung remix of Digital & Spirit’s ‘Phantom Force’, the hands-in-the-air thrills of 2014’s award winning and cross over ‘Loving Touch’ and 2015’s collaboration with Manchester’s Chimpo on Metalheadz. 2016’s Hype Tracks EP on Exit Records - including a collaboration with Teklife’s Spinn & Taso - furthers the blend and was play-listed by Beats1 and Apple Radio. Fracture has also been sighted in the studio alongside likeminded contemporaries including Bristol’s Sam Binga, fellow veteran Kid Drama, and in 2016 with an array of Exit artists and guest vocalists as part of the Richie Brains supergroup. From stripped back rhythmic workouts to sweaty dancehall riddims via emotive compositions and catchy sample flips, Fracture’s music has a little of everything.

Astrophonica also embraces this open-minded ethic. Focused on releasing music across a spectrum of tempos it has been home to Dawn Day Night, Machinedrum, Om Unit, and Fracture’s collaboration with Sam Binga and Rider Shafique. It’s also given a platform to new talents, including the dub-wise sensibilities of Paris’ Moresounds, the junglistic chops of Sully and the unmistakable and unique live instrumentation of Tehbis & Touchy Subject. 2017’s ‘Gradients’ saw Fracture curate the label’s first various artists compilation with appearances from Astrophonica regulars, newcomers and heavy hitting guests including dBridge, Stray and a collaboration with Teklife’s DJ Earl.  ‘Gradients’ encapsulates and solidifies the sound which Fracture has pushed through Astrophonica since its conception and this curating mentality has seen him provide mixes for BBC R1, Solid Steel, XLR8R and Fact and start his own live mix series ‘Broadcast’. Astrophonica is a home for daring artists, who share the same flair for rhythm and space, disposition for risk-taking and thirst for the new that keep Fracture moving forward.

Jacob Korn from Dresden, Germany was born in the early 80's. His sound is influenced by Kraftwerk and the sound of 90's techno and house music. He has been producing electronic music of different flavours for what seems like an eternity. Early on in his career he combined Hip Hop and Techno with elements of Jazz and weird electronics under the Granufunk moniker.

Once he turned his attention to more classical but versatile house and techno stylings he chose to go by his given name. Jacob Korn continually experiments in new recordingstyles and production techniques, while developing his own music tools for cross mediaarts and interactive performances.

He played live in clubs and at festivals in Japan (Ageha-Tokyo, Triangle-Osaka), Chile (Mutek-Santiago), Uruguay (Soco-Montevideo), Canada (Mutek-Montrel, New Forms-Vancouver, RBMA-Toronto), USA (HoneySound-San Francisco, Mr.Sunday-NYC) Spain (Sonár Festival-Barcelona), Norway, Denmark (Dunkel-Copenhagen), Netherlands (Sugar Factory, Picnic at Night-Amsterdam), Sweden, Switzerland (Zukunft-Zürich), Austria and Germany (Panoramabar/Berghain,  Watergate, About/Blank, Kleine Reise-Berlin, Ego and Übel und Gefährlich-Hamburg, Robert Johnson-Offenbach, Bob Beaman-München, CynetartFestival-Dresden, MELT!-Festival Nachtdigital Festival).

Jacob Korn released his debut album, different EPs and remixes under various names on international Labels like Astrolab, Running Back, Permanent Vacation, Basic Soul Units "Left of the dial" and Panorama Bar Resident Steffis "Dolly"-Imprint. New Releases for Uncanny Valley are coming this year, so keep your ears pricked up.

Toys For Boys Records is a leading and respected underground music label, with a strong presence in the European house and techno scenes.
Founded in 2004 by Marcus Vector and Sierra_Sam, the Brussels/Berlin based imprint has been gathering artists such as Quenum, Sarah Goldfarb, Mark Broom, Tom Dazing, or Grinser with remix collaborations from the likes of Paul Ritch, Tim Xavier or Dan Curtin.
Toys for Boys’ name is in itself a kind of a private joke, meaning "boys are geeks and like to play with electronic toys to make music"...Its musical inclinations are open to a variety of techno sounds scattered with electronica and house influences. With a dancefloor orientation on each release the label's guiding principle is that "there is a space for creativity in between the 4x4 beat”…

Reigning the Walloon region in Belgium, in Liège, LeftRight Audio Studio is under the command of Audio Engineer Dan D’Ascenzo, who is dealing with creative Mastering and Mixing, as well as sound design, music and beat making.

It is a warm location in a green area surrounded by nature, hosting lots of workshops, group & private sessions, as well as attended individual projects.

Strategically located between Germany, Holland and Belgium, Leftright Studio positions itself among the high-end mastering studios worldwide and presents itself with carefully selected gear from the best brands like Dangerous Music, SPL, Antelope and others (for more details feel free to check the detailed list presented under equipment).

Dan has been in the field for more than 15 years, both practicing and as a lecturer in SAE Institute. He is well known for his warm, human approach of the projects he works on and in the relationship with his clients. His creative style applies to all genres of music and artists as long as there is emotion in the productions which he then brings to another level.
